---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<section class="sec sec--console shot" aria-labelledby="shot-title">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="head">
      <p class="eyebrow">// transmission · 02</p>
      <h2 id="shot-title" class="head-title">
        <span class="mono">The whole loop,</span>
        <span class="display">one window.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="head-lede">
        Open a project. Pick your agent. Describe a feature. Review diffs,
        stage changes, commit — without ever switching context.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="caption">
      <p class="cap-eyebrow">// signal · 01 · the cockpit</p>
      <h3 class="cap-title">Chat, editor, terminal, Git — one window.</h3>
      <p class="cap-body">
        The SAI desktop with a project loaded. Chat sits beside a full Monaco
        editor, an integrated PTY terminal runs below, and Git status lives in
        the sidebar. Everything you need for the prompt → review → ship loop is
        on screen at once.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="screen brackets">
      <span class="br-tr"></span><span class="br-bl"></span>
      <header class="screen-bar">
        <span class="lbl">CHANNEL · 01</span>
        <span class="lbl">RES · 1400×900</span>
        <span class="lbl ok">● LIVE</span>
        <span class="lbl mar" data-time>--:--:--</span>
      </header>
      <div class="img-wrap">
        <img src={`${base}img/screenshot.png`} alt="SAI desktop showing chat, editor, terminal, and Git panels" width="1400" height="900" loading="lazy" />
        <span class="aberration" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="scanlines" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tr" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-bl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-br" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
      </div>
      <footer class="screen-foot">
        <span>FRAME · 00:01:24:08</span>
        <span>EXPOSURE · AUTO</span>
        <span>GAIN · +0db</span>
        <span class="ml">CAM · 01/A</span>
      </footer>
    </figure>

    <div class="caption">
      <p class="cap-eyebrow">// signal · 02 · the agent loop</p>
      <h3 class="cap-title">Streaming output, queued prompts, inline approvals.</h3>
      <p class="cap-body">
        Another angle on the cockpit. Token meters and a turn timer keep the
        agent honest, the composer queues follow-up prompts behind the
        streaming turn, and tool calls land in an approval panel — no flipping
        tabs to stay in control.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="screen brackets alt">
      <span class="br-tr"></span><span class="br-bl"></span>
      <header class="screen-bar">
        <span class="lbl">CHANNEL · 02</span>
        <span class="lbl">RES · 1400×900</span>
        <span class="lbl ok">● LIVE</span>
        <span class="lbl mar" data-time-b>--:--:--</span>
      </header>
      <div class="img-wrap">
        <img src={`${base}img/screenshot-2.png`} alt="SAI showing another view of the editor, chat, and tooling" width="1400" height="900" loading="lazy" />
        <span class="aberration" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="scanlines" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tr" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-bl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-br" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
      </div>
      <footer class="screen-foot">
        <span>FRAME · 00:02:48:12</span>
        <span>EXPOSURE · AUTO</span>
        <span>GAIN · +0db</span>
        <span class="ml">CAM · 02/B</span>
      </footer>
    </figure>

    <div class="caption">
      <p class="cap-eyebrow">// signal · 03 · swarm mode</p>
      <h3 class="cap-title">Five tasks dispatched. All green. Land the batch.</h3>
      <p class="cap-body">
        The Swarm sidebar after a 5-task burst. Each task ran in its own git
        worktree on a <code>swarm/…</code> branch, streamed live, and reported
        diff stats when it finished. Hit <strong>Land all green</strong> to
        fast-forward every clean task into the base branch — or open any row to
        review its diff one at a time.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="screen brackets">
      <span class="br-tr"></span><span class="br-bl"></span>
      <header class="screen-bar">
        <span class="lbl">CHANNEL · 03</span>
        <span class="lbl">RES · 1400×900</span>
        <span class="lbl ok">● LIVE</span>
        <span class="lbl mar" data-time-c>--:--:--</span>
      </header>
      <div class="img-wrap">
        <img src={`${base}img/swarm.png`} alt="SAI Swarm mode: orchestrator chat with a 5-task batch complete and a 'Land all green' button" width="1400" height="900" loading="lazy" />
        <span class="aberration" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="scanlines" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tr" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-bl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-br" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
      </div>
      <footer class="screen-foot">
        <span>FRAME · 00:04:12:03</span>
        <span>EXPOSURE · AUTO</span>
        <span>GAIN · +0db</span>
        <span class="ml">CAM · 03/SWARM</span>
      </footer>
    </figure>

    <div class="caption">
      <p class="cap-eyebrow">// signal · 04 · meta workspaces</p>
      <h3 class="cap-title">One workspace. Many repos. One conversation.</h3>
      <p class="cap-body">
        A meta workspace named <em>AI Dev Tools</em> with two repos
        (<code>sai</code>, <code>tai</code>) wired in. The chat, terminal, and
        editor all span every included project; the Git panel renders
        independent stage / commit / push / pull controls per repo so
        cross-cutting changes happen in one place — without sharing one
        branch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="screen brackets">
      <span class="br-tr"></span><span class="br-bl"></span>
      <header class="screen-bar">
        <span class="lbl">CHANNEL · 04</span>
        <span class="lbl">RES · 1400×900</span>
        <span class="lbl ok">● LIVE</span>
        <span class="lbl mar" data-time-d>--:--:--</span>
      </header>
      <div class="img-wrap">
        <img src={`${base}img/meta.png`} alt="SAI Meta workspace 'AI Dev Tools' with two repos in the Git sidebar, each with their own commit/push/pull controls" width="1400" height="900" loading="lazy" />
        <span class="aberration" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="scanlines" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-tr" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-bl" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        <span class="reticle reticle-br" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
      </div>
      <footer class="screen-foot">
        <span>FRAME · 00:05:36:17</span>
        <span>EXPOSURE · AUTO</span>
        <span>GAIN · +0db</span>
        <span class="ml">CAM · 04/META</span>
      </footer>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const targets = document.querySelectorAll('[data-time], [data-time-b], [data-time-c], [data-time-d]');
    if (targets.length) {
      const upd = () => {
        const d = new Date();
        const t = [d.getHours(), d.getMinutes(), d.getSeconds()]
          .map(n => String(n).padStart(2, '0')).join(':');
        targets.forEach(el => { el.textContent = t; });
      };
      upd(); setInterval(upd, 1000);
    }
  </script>
</section>

<style>
  .shot { padding-bottom: 120px; }
  .head { max-width: 880px; margin-bottom: 64px; }
  .head .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 22px; }
  .head-title {
    display: grid; gap: 6px;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.6vw, 3.8rem);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .head-title .mono { font-family: var(--mono); color: var(--phosphor); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .head-title .display { font-family: var(--display); font-style: italic; color: var(--phosphor-2); font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.015em; }
  .head-lede { margin-top: 22px; max-width: 60ch; color: var(--phosphor-2); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; }

  .screen {
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    background: #08090b;
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
    box-shadow:
      inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,180,84,0.06),
      0 50px 120px -40px rgba(255,180,84,0.25);
  }
  .screen + .screen { margin-top: 48px; }

  .caption { max-width: 760px; margin: 64px 0 24px; }
  .caption:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
  .cap-eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
  }
  .cap-title {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.8vw, 1.35rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--phosphor);
  }
  .cap-body {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--phosphor-2);
    opacity: 0.82;
  }
  .cap-body code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.95em;
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    color: var(--phosphor);
    background: rgba(255,180,84,0.04);
  }
  .cap-body strong { color: var(--phosphor); font-weight: 700; }
  .cap-body em { color: var(--phosphor); font-style: italic; }
  .screen-bar, .screen-foot {
    display: flex; gap: 28px; align-items: center;
    padding: 12px 18px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--phosphor-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .screen-foot { border-bottom: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .screen-bar .ok { color: var(--green); }
  .screen-bar .mar { margin-left: auto; color: var(--phosphor); }
  .screen-foot .ml { margin-left: auto; color: var(--phosphor); }

  .img-wrap { position: relative; }
  .img-wrap img {
    display: block; width: 100%; height: auto;
    filter: contrast(1.02) saturate(1.05);
  }
  .scanlines {
    position: absolute; inset: 0; pointer-events: none;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      transparent 0,
      transparent 2px,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.18) 2px,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.18) 3px
    );
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
  }
  .aberration {
    position: absolute; inset: 0; pointer-events: none;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at center, transparent 50%, rgba(0,0,0,0.55) 100%);
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
  }
  .reticle {
    position: absolute; color: var(--phosphor); font-family: var(--mono); font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 22px; line-height: 1; padding: 4px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(255,180,84,0.5);
  }
  .reticle-tl { top: 12px; left: 12px; }
  .reticle-tr { top: 12px; right: 12px; }
  .reticle-bl { bottom: 12px; left: 12px; }
  .reticle-br { bottom: 12px; right: 12px; }
</style>
